# Security Rules (Non-Negotiable)

## Backend Controllers

- ALL controllers MUST have `[Authorize]` attribute (except health endpoints)
- ALWAYS forward user's `Authorization` header to Supabase (preserves RLS)
- NEVER bypass Row Level Security
- Use service role key ONLY for admin operations AND verify caller's admin role first

## Error Status Codes

- `401`: Missing/invalid token
- `403`: Insufficient permissions
- `422`: Bad request payload
- **`502`**: Downstream (Supabase) error - NOT 500!
- `500`: Internal server error only

## General Security

- NEVER commit secrets/API keys
- Use `.env.local` (gitignored) for local secrets
- Always validate user permissions before operations
